From mossman Amy Mossman Subject Re Is MSG sensitivity superstition In article Doug Bank writes Here is another anecdotal I am a picky eater and never wanted to try chinese food however I finally tried some in order to please a girl I was seeing at the I had never heard of Chinese restaurant A group of us went to the restaurant and all shared different It didn't taste great but I decided it wasn't so We went home and went to bed I woke up at AM and puked my guts I threw up for so long that I'm not kidding I pulled a muscle in my Dry heaves and No one else got sick and I'm not allergic to anything that I know Suffice to say that I wont go into a chinese restaurant unless I am physically The smell of the food makes me ill and that is a psycholgical reaction When I have been dragged in to suffer through beef and broccoli without any sauces I insist on no I haven't gotten sick I had a similar reaction to Chinese food but came to a completly different I've eaten Chinese food for ages and never had I went with some Chinese Malaysian friends to a swanky Chinses and they ordered lots of stuff I had never seen The only thing I can remember of that meal was the first course scallops served in the shell with a soy type I thought Well I've only had scallops once and I was sick after but that could have been a coincidence That night as I sat on the bathroom floor sweating and emptying my stomach the hard way I decided I would never touch another I may not be allergic but I don't want to take the Amy Mossman